    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="855"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d855">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.24/114</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Yugoslav Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fotitch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-21">September 21,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of September 19, 1939, informing me that your Government contemplates
                    purchasing a large quantity of arms, ammunition, and implements of war in the
                    United States.</p>
                <p>I have taken due note of your assurance that these arms, ammunition, and
                    implements of war are intended solely for the use of the Yugoslav Army.</p>
                <p>Prompt consideration will be given to any application which the Department may
                    receive for licenses to export these arms, ammunition, and implements of
                    war.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
